<span id="freeTextContainer8091155768221485472">I respect your review and I 100% believe you feel as you do, but objectively speaking, I don&apos;t think the grammatical issues were nearly as bad as you </span>
  <span id="freeText8091155768221485472" style="display:none">I respect your review and I 100% believe you feel as you do, but objectively speaking, I don't think the grammatical issues were nearly as bad as you make it seem. The example you brought up with the bell was very easy to understand. Nobody would think he meant the belt in that scenario. If you did, that's a personal comprehension issue. I mean, how did all these other people manage to understand everything perfectly fine? I think you can understand it perfectly fine for the most part too, but just that you care about grammar to a level above normal. Am I right that you might be exaggerating because of your specific bias, or do you genuinely believe it's bad to the point of being unreadable?</span>
